metadata.name: Protein #31
metadata.description:
Exploration of noise fields.

The project is written in vanilla Javascript.

The drawing is executed at window resolution.

Press '2' to double the resolution. You can press again '2' to double once more;
Press '1' to get back at the window size.
Press 's' to save a png at the current resolution. You can also right click and 'save-as' to obtain the same result.


It uses 3 external packages, both licensed under MIT license:

* https://www.npmjs.com/package/simplex-noise
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/file-saver
* https://www.npmjs.com/package/alea

metadata.name: Iris #48
metadata.description:
Iris was a totally unexpected topic ! It was "discovered" during the development of my previous projects. What is really interesting me is the appearance of a shape which is partially achieved and quite unregular and seems to be an iris. Then, I add two mains features in order to increase diversity : 

- overlapping of different kind of iris basement with a variable depth towards the center. In some cases, this generates a restraint area around the pupil with additional colors, brightness or darkness, which makes the iris even more complex. In other cases, the iris is enriched with so many colors that it can even result in giving the appearance of flowers. Picture what it would be like if it were for real ! I may buy some contact lenses now...


- the outside of the iris. Instead of being purely white like an eye-ball, there is an assembly of colorfull weavings that may emphasize the iris presence as if there was an oculus. But, the door would be quite softened since it is based on a weaving process. On the contrary, there is also a zoom feature that brings you closer to the iris and then makes you focus on the detals around the pupil.

I hope those pieces will bring you as much fun as it does me !

metadata.name: A Slight Case of Overbombing #44
metadata.description:
Inspired by monochromatic art of the late 60s, Russian folk-art woodblock prints, and the stylised colours of British underground comics, excited to introduce a series of bold rich landscapes. England, Wales, Ireland and Scotland represented by red, yellow, green and blue, sometimes a house or two, and groovy clouds.

Instructions ::

.     - speed up
,     - slow down
space - pause
n     - toggle noise
p     - cycle palette
h     - toggle high-res (and definitely intentional pixel shift)
s     - download and save image

metadata.name: Industrial #59
Oceans of Anxiety #15
metadata.description:
Fully generated by code on your machine. Variety of palletes and styles hand-picked with love and understanding.

Anxiety comes in waves.
It’s that sense of unidentifiable dread.
It can feel like you’re in the middle of an ocean on a rocking boat, and on those really bad days there isn’t even a lifebuoy, you’re drowning and can’t catch your breath, time is viscous and moving in slow-motion.

This piece does not set out to necessarily convey only the worst of dealing with anxiety, but also the resolutions and relief when it’s not there, or finally lets you go.

metadata.name: MOBO // HASH #53
metadata.description:
A generative exploration of the MOBO kind.

My goal here was simple... to create a series of pieces that I would genuinely want to collect myself. Style, color, the odd pop culture reference, and a nod to some of my earlier pieces/characters. I sincerely hope you enjoy this collection.

These characters are made up of more than 100 PNG layers. The under-the-hood wizardry is courtesy of the PureSpider FXHASH PFP Token Generator.

2k x 2k resolution.
